{
  "doc_id": "33429",
  "text": "To kill or condition C. elegans, EPEC use a secreted factor or factors, production of which requires both tryptophan in the media and the bacterial tryptophanase gene tnaA [CITATION_1] . Tryptophanase converts tryptophan into indole, ammonia, and pyruvate, which allows EPEC, EHEC and other E. coli to utilize tryptophan as the sole source of carbon and nitrogen [CITATION_2] . Indole is a metabolite synthesized and secreted by E. coli that regulates biofilm formation [CITATION_3] , and facilitates inter-and intracellular signaling [CITATION_4] as well as adaptation to stressors [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] .",
